In article <31hbvs$58n@crl4.crl.com>, Wayne Hoxsie <hoxsiew@crl.com> wrote:
>Ken Pizzini (ken@chinook.halcyon.com) wrote:
>: 25 iterations of a modified DES on eight NULs.
>	What is the SALT value used for?

The salt determines which of a set of 4096 modification to DES to use.
In particular, it selects a permutation of the expansion table.

